\begin{theorem}
Let $a,b\in\NN$ and let $p\in\NN$ be prime.
Suppose $p\divides ab$.
Then $a$, $b$ are coprime if and only if
$p$ divides $a$ or $p$ divides $b$ but $p$ does not divide both.
\end{theorem}

