\begin{theorem}
Let $\pi$ be a set of primes, $G$ be a finite group, $H\subgroup G$ be
a subgroup.
Then $H$ is a Hall $\pi$-subgroup if and only if
every prime divisor $p\divides|G|$ divides exactly one of $|H|$ or $\Index{G}{H}$.
\end{theorem}

